text: Dereham is a town in Norfolk, England, sometimes called East Dereham Dereham may also refer to: * West Dereham, village in Norfolk, England * Elias of Dereham (died 1246), English master stonemason * Francis Dereham (c.1513–1541), English courtier * Sir Thomas Dereham, 4th Baronet (c.1678–1739), English scientist and Jacobite ==See also== * Derham (disambiguation) * Battle of Deorham
title: Dereham (disambiguation)
